      "content": "It sounds like your exhaustion might not be about the places you've seen, but the relentless pace of discovery itself. Sometimes the most restful journey isn't another destination, but finally stopping the movement entirely and letting everything settle. There is immense strength and worth in simply resting without the pressure to find new meanings or \"new ways\" to look at the world.",
      "source": "target",
